description: I originally posted this on my personal page, but wanted to post it here because I just love it so much and thought you may too 🥰. This was one of my favorite movies as a kid, if not my favorite movie. To this day, if it's on tv, I have to sit and watch it all. Who knew that it subconsciously inspired me with Coastal Cowboy. When I'm saying we're all inspired in ways we may not even realize, this is what I mean. I had no idea the pieces of inspiration that were plucked from this movie that I've held on to all these years. Being born and raised in California, and having an Uncle that’s a cattle rancher, and living not far from Napa, I always thought it was so cool how they filmed in Napa.  I also longed to visit London and looked up to the classic, timeless and beautiful style of how women dressed in Europe.  I think that was when this Coastal Cowboy seed was planted. 🤍 #coastalcowboy #coastalcowboybrand #coastalstyle #coastalcowgirl #coastalvibes #summertrends2023 #springtrends2023 #coastalcowboyhomedecor #timelessstyle

Igual puede usar botas de hule que estilo es el pantalón trae buen corte para bota pero tiene gamusa no son muy sucias saludos Son muy cómodas no sirto si en el rancho para eso se usan botas de trabajo no vaqueras

description: One year of Coastal Cowboy. It all started with a small decorative cowboy hat and here we are 🥹 I was born & raised in CA and lived there for 31 years before moving to Tennessee. My background is in Advertising Photography, but as a kid I had always dreamed of owning a product based business and becoming a designer one day, so that always kind of stuck with me in the back of my mind. Coastal Cowboy was born out the feeling of homesickness blended with the beauty and freedom of Tennessee. It’s not only a love letter to the nostalgia of where I grew up, but also hugely inspired by my Uncle who is a cattle rancher back in California. There’s so much more I want to create with this very small business so i hope you’ll follow along 🫶🏼 #coastalcowboy

It’s our one year anniversary!! One full year of coastal cowboy since we launched our first product 🥹. Our decorative cowboy hats and custom scented candle came out 4.18.23 and it has been a total rollercoaster since! Coastal Cowboy is the blend of many parts of my world, all wrapped up into a thoughtfully and meticulously designed lifestyle brand and is constantly evolving as I learn more about myself, my family heritage, and growing as a creative person. It’s not only a love letter to the nostalgia of where I grew up, but also hugely inspired by my Uncle who is a cattle rancher back in California. Growing up I always loved going to his ranch, being around the horses, having to get there by a dirt road, the wide open spaces with no street lights, abandoned barns, old school western style decor, I just loved all of that and it left a significant mark on me. Combined with my love of going to Big Sur, Carmel, Half Moon Bay, and other places along the CA coast was the start of Coastal Cowboy. But, with that being said, Coastal Cowboy is so much more than a cowboy hat on the beach, to me. #coastalcowboy #coastalcowgirl

description: It’s horse girl summer y’all 🐴🤍🌾 #fyp #cowgirl #westernstyle #ootd #yeehaw #horsegirl #summeroutfits #styleinspo #cowgirlboots

Last month I celebrated one year of the first products going live! Coastal Cowboy started from nothing. It started before “coastal cowgirl” was a term. I easily could have called this “coastal cowgirl” becuase it didnt exist yet, but I chose not to do that. Why? Becuase it felt like a trend, it felt like a throw away name, it felt too on-the-nose, too easy, and not what I was trying to build.  I coined the Coastal Cowboy name, thoughtfully paired with a curated aesthetic I put together, and have seen it take off in ways I never expected.  It has been a really hard journey if I am allowed to be honest. I’ve had many people steal from me, call me names, tell me this isn’t mine, copy our products, not give us credit, etc. I almost have quit this a million times. But I know in my heart we are the originators and I’ll continue to pursue this brand with everything I have left in me. So thank you to those who have been with us from the beginning. 💙 #coastalcowboy #coastalcowgirl
